ption may cause problems if class files aren't present. The test might even fail in a native environment where `getCodeSource()` could return null. Plus, existing dynamic class loading with ByteBuddy handles errors poorly. If native throws UnsupportedFeatureError instead, I should keep that in mind while detecting if itâ€™s being run in a native setting.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Rethinking isolated loaders for native**\\n\\nI'm considering whether to avoid using an isolated loader for the native environment by relying on a public API. In my top test, I could try running `runInIsolated` and catch UnsupportedFeatureError. However, if I encounter ClassNotFoundException, that could be tricky since native images typically donâ€™t support URLClassLoader. It might lead to NullPointerException if `getCodeSource` is null. To be cautious, I should first run an in-process scenario; just confirming the order of tests might be crucial to avoid issues in native.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring direct scenarios in native environments**\\n\\nIâ€™m thinking about how a direct scenario might behave under native conditions. If it doesnâ€™t throw an error until after setting UsingUnsafe, then it might see safety as false when ByteBuddy generates a class, leading to an unsupported Error. In the JVM, if UsingUnsafe initializes too late, it could throw an AssertionError because it returns true. Maybe I should focus on direct scenarios only in native, as catching AssertionError might not help if UsingUnsafe turns out to be unavailable.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_v5HKSnOM7kZvcCqhfQFWd4An|fc_05ae0ab35c02adcb0169fbff15b8548196ac8f33a7e135618f", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.modelmapper/modelmapper/3.2.0/src/test/java/org_modelmapper/modelmapper/ClassInjectorInnerUsingReflectionInnerDispatcherInnerUsingUnsafeOverrideTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    @Test\n    void injectsGeneratedClassesThroughUnsafeOverrideDispatcher() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            runInIsolatedModelMapperLoader();\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        } catch (UnsupportedOperationException exception) {\n            assertThat(exception.getMessage())\n                    .startsWith(\"Cannot \")\n                    .contains(\" using reflection: \");\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void runInIsolatedModelMapperLoader() throws Exception {\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void injectsGeneratedClassesThroughUnsafeOverrideDispatcher() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            runWithUnsafeOverrideDispatcher();\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        } catch (UnsupportedOperationException exception) {\n            assertThat(exception.getMessage())\n                    .startsWith(\"Cannot \")\n                    .contains(\" using reflection: \");\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void runWithUnsafeOverrideDispatcher() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            new UnsafeOverrideDispatcherScenario().run();\n        } catch (AssertionError error) {\n            if (!\"UsingUnsafe should be unavailable in the isolated loader\"\n                    .equals(error.getMessage())) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n            runInIsolatedModelMapperLoader();\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void runInIsolatedModelMapperLoader() throws Exception {\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 222, "output": 1342, "cacheRead": 61440, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 63004, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778122502229, "responseId": "resp_05ae0ab35c02adcb0169fbff0729a481969f5333605e94e050"