[assistant] Fixed the native-image compile failure caused by the test subclassing `UsingReflection`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] The issue was that the JUnit native feature recursively inspects nested/superclass metadata for test classes. The helper subclass of `UsingReflection` caused it to inspect ModelMapper/ByteBuddy internals and load a nested type requiring `com.sun.jna.Library`, which is not on the classpath.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Updated:
[assistant] 
[assistant] `tests/src/org.modelmapper/modelmapper/3.2.0/src/test/java/org_modelmapper/modelmapper/ClassInjectorInnerUsingReflectionInnerDispatcherInnerUsingUnsafeOverrideTest.java`
[assistant] 
[assistant] Changes:
[assistant] - Removed the `ReflectionAccess extends UsingReflection` helper class.
[assistant] - Switched back to direct use of `UsingReflection.Dispatcher` and `Dispatcher.Initializable`.
[assistant] - Kept the same dispatcher scenario logic without introducing a test class inheritance relationship to ModelMapper internals.
[assistant] 
[assistant] This should avoid native-imageâ€™s JUnit test-class registrar traversing into the JNA-dependent ByteBuddy nested classes.
[assistant-event] text_end
